      "date": "2019-06-28 22:00:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Do you have a sense of why the test wasn't failing 100%?  Or was\n > there a config where it was?\n\nI don't understand why it wasn't previously failing either.  Possibly non-full runs were not enabling ea_inode properly, or otherwise not advertising a full 64KB for llite.*.max_easize, and the test is only going to try and write an xattr up to max_easize bytes.\n\nI changed the test to print max_xattr_size in the output so we can see this in the future if it fails again.",
